        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 3:58PM EDT until July 1 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Chatham, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsfield, Great Barrington, Chatham, New Lebanon, Austerlitz,
Philmont, Housatonic, Ghent, Stockbridge, Canaan, Richmond, West
Stockbridge, Alford, Barkerville, Glendale, Rayville, North
Hillsdale, Williamsville, Harlemville, and North Egremont.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
